   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER THREE THE LIVING IN THE BODY OF CHRIST Scripture Reading: Eph 5:23; Col 3:4a, 11b; 1 Cor 12:12; Eph 1:23; Phil 3:14; Eph 4:4a; 1 John 5:6; Phil 4:12b; Rom 15:13; 6:6; 8:13b; Gal 5:24; Eph 2:6a; Phil 3:10a; 1 John 5:11-12; Rom 9:11b; Gal 2:16a; Phil 1:19-21a; Rom 12:5 OUTLINE Taking Christ as its Head, life, content, principal object, center, and goal: As its Head, life, and content Eph 5:23; Col 3:4a, 11b: Concerning Christ as the source and element of His Body.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Referring to the origin and being of the Body of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>As its principal object, center, and goal 1 Cor 12:12; Eph 1:23; Phil 3:14: Concerning Christ as the meaning and expression of His Body.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Referring to the capacity and function of the Body of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Having the Spirit as its essence and reality, and taking the Spirit as its secret and effectiveness: As its essence and reality Eph 4:4a; 1 John 5:6: Concerning the inward nature and the real outward state of the Body of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Referring to the inward being and the outward manifestation of the Body of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>As its secret and effectiveness Phil 4:12b; Rom 15:13: Concerning the skill and ability of the Body of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Referring to the skillfulness and achievements of the Body of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Taking the crucifixion and resurrection of Christ as its regulation: Being regulated in the negative aspect by the crucifixion of Christ: Our crucifixion with Christ being an accomplished fact realized through divine revelation Rom 6:6.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Our crucifixion with Christ being the day-to-day experience that we that should have enjoyed through the effectiveness of the Spirit Rom 8:13b; Gal 5:24.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Being regulated in the positive aspect by the resurrection of Christ: Our resurrection with Christ being an accomplished fact Eph 2:6a.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Our resurrection with Christ being the day-to-day experience that we should have Phil 3:10a.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Taking life and the Body as the principle: Taking life as the principle: Taking the inward life of God, which is just Christ as the embodiment of God, as the principle 1 John 5:11-12.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Not taking the outward conduct and morality of man as the principle Rom 9:11b; Gal 2:16a.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Taking the Body as the principle: Every member living Christ out by the Spirit of life Phil 1:19-21a.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Living corporately and coordinating to live out the Body of Christ to be the fullness of Christ to express Him Rom 12:5; Eph 1:23.</S>
   </TEXT>
